  "texts": [
    "As noted above, while the IKS state breaks moiré translations, it does so in a \"spiral\" fashion that does not lead to a moiré-scale modulation of the electron density.",
    "As such, rather than working with fully translational-breaking Hartree-Fock, we can instead work in a 'boosted' coordinate system where the Γ-points of valleys K and K ′ are shifted by an amount ±q IVC /2 with respect to each other, and treat q IVC as a variational parameter 57.",
    "In other words, we chooseP τ ′ bs ′ k β,τ ask α ≡ ⟨ĉ † τ as (k α)ĉ τ ′ bs ′ (k β)⟩ ∼ δ ss ′ δ k α +τ qIVC/2,k β +τ ′ qIVC/2(100)where τ = ±1 for K and K ′ valley respectively, and the Kronecker deltas on the RHS enforce spin-collinearity 58, and the constraint that any IVC must occur with spiral wavevector q IVC 59.",
    "For convenience and to make contact with our previous notation, we now define a new set of operators ĉ † τ as (k) = ĉ † τ as (kτ q IVC /2), so that (throughout this subsection, we denote quantities with respect to this new set of momenta labels with a tilde)Pτ ′ bs ′ k β,τ ask α ≡ ⟨ ĉ † τ as (k α) ĉτ ′ bs ′ (k β)⟩ ∝ δ ss ′ δ k α,k β.",
    "(101)This block-diagonal structure allows us to write the one-particle density matrix exactly as before, but with c-operators replacing c-operators:Pτ ′ b,τ a (k, s) ≡ ⟨ ĉ † τ as (k) ĉτ ′ bs (k)⟩."
